WEBVTT

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:37.480
Now this is what I love about high school parties.

00:00:37.820 --> 00:00:39.460
People will gather anywhere as long as there's

00:00:39.460 --> 00:00:41.420
illegally purchased alcohol and even the slightest

00:00:41.420 --> 00:00:43.340
chance of cooking up. If I recall correctly,

00:00:43.340 --> 00:00:44.780
you're the one who wanted to come to this party.

00:00:45.740 --> 00:00:47.920
Yeah, but I didn't know it was going to be so cold.

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:50.039
It's like 20,000 degrees below zero out here.

00:00:50.480 --> 00:00:51.840
I don't know. It doesn't feel that cold to me.

00:00:52.039 --> 00:00:53.219
What are you, from an ice pillar?

00:00:53.320 --> 00:00:56.060
It's freezing. I'm going to go thaw out by the fire.

00:00:57.780 --> 00:00:58.260
Have fun.

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:10.079
Hey, Kent.

00:01:11.620 --> 00:01:12.640
Are you friends with Chloe?

00:01:12.640 --> 00:01:14.040
Chloe, is she flying solo tonight?

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:16.260
Believe me, Sean, you're not her type.

00:01:21.400 --> 00:01:22.439
Well, you'd be surprised.

00:01:29.280 --> 00:01:29.980
If you want to come,

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:30.879
I could rub them for you.

00:01:31.959 --> 00:01:33.799
But nothing heats up a body like friction.

00:01:37.379 --> 00:01:37.780
Wow.

00:01:38.500 --> 00:01:40.239
I can't believe you just delivered that line

00:01:40.239 --> 00:01:41.280
with a straight face.

00:01:41.460 --> 00:01:43.620
Well, all I did was offer to keep your hands warm, Chloe.

00:01:44.280 --> 00:01:45.659
And he knows my name.

00:01:46.060 --> 00:01:47.719
I've read your editorials in The Torch.

00:01:49.719 --> 00:01:50.359
Pretty cool.

00:01:51.060 --> 00:01:51.900
Well, thank you, Sean.

00:01:52.599 --> 00:01:54.280
I sit next to Jenna in bio class.

00:01:54.719 --> 00:01:56.579
Remember you dumped her last week?

00:01:57.000 --> 00:01:57.719
It was mutual.

00:01:58.719 --> 00:01:59.980
So you're here trolling,

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:01.000
and you're here for a freshman.

00:02:02.040 --> 00:02:02.959
Don't worry, Chloe.

00:02:03.180 --> 00:02:04.500
I'm not going to make a move on you.

00:02:05.420 --> 00:02:06.900
No matter how pretty I think you are.

00:02:08.060 --> 00:02:08.639
Hey, Sean.

00:02:09.120 --> 00:02:10.240
Hail Mary's down by the lake.

00:02:11.280 --> 00:02:11.620
Yeah.

00:02:14.020 --> 00:02:14.919
Hey, can I get your number?

00:02:16.259 --> 00:02:17.599
Why? You're never going to call.

00:02:17.900 --> 00:02:18.759
I'll call you tomorrow.

00:02:19.560 --> 00:02:20.259
I promise.

00:02:21.539 --> 00:02:22.819
Well, I won't go back on it.

00:02:30.000 --> 00:02:35.219
Come on, Sean. Let's go.

00:02:35.280 --> 00:02:36.080
Hey, Whitney. Back pass.

00:02:37.659 --> 00:02:38.340
Come on. Let's go.

00:02:38.340 --> 00:02:39.340
Come on.

00:02:50.599 --> 00:02:52.439
Did you just write your phone number down

00:02:52.439 --> 00:02:53.460
on Sean Calvin's hand?

00:02:54.900 --> 00:02:56.099
Don't sound so shocked, Clark.

00:02:56.520 --> 00:02:58.099
Guys do find me attractive even though

00:02:58.099 --> 00:02:59.960
I don't have raven hair on me and issues out.

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:00.500
Oh.

00:03:00.500 --> 00:03:01.500
That's not what I meant.

00:03:02.120 --> 00:03:02.840
There's a dog.

00:03:03.259 --> 00:03:04.259
Clark, relax.

00:03:05.120 --> 00:03:06.620
I just gave him my number to get rid of him.

00:03:07.180 --> 00:03:07.680
Get Pete.

00:03:08.060 --> 00:03:09.060
The taxi's leaving.

00:03:14.180 --> 00:03:16.020
So what's with you and that Chloe Sullivan chick?

00:03:16.259 --> 00:03:17.020
What do you mean?

00:03:17.020 --> 00:03:18.099
She's the girl from the tour.

00:03:18.099 --> 00:03:18.860
Did you into her?

00:03:19.520 --> 00:03:20.719
Another notch, dog.

00:03:21.740 --> 00:03:22.599
That's cold.

00:03:26.060 --> 00:03:27.060
Hey, hold on. Pete's here.

00:03:29.139 --> 00:03:29.979
Sorry, dude.

00:03:30.500 --> 00:03:31.240
Uh, go ahead.

00:03:32.060 --> 00:03:33.080
I'll get the ball.

00:03:39.800 --> 00:03:40.759
Whoa!

00:03:44.939 --> 00:03:45.900
inch

00:03:47.159 --> 00:03:47.960
ø

00:03:51.840 --> 00:03:53.479
That's not a bird.

00:03:56.680 --> 00:03:58.560
I don't have to wait.

00:03:58.560 --> 00:03:59.580
Let's see what changes

00:03:59.580 --> 00:03:59.979
that will make our aging dog station appear.

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:21.480
Hey, where's Sean?

00:04:22.019 --> 00:04:23.720
He was probably in the back of some car.

00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:32.000
No!

00:04:32.860 --> 00:04:33.860
No!

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:02.000
No!

00:05:30.000 --> 00:05:30.860
No!

00:05:54.720 --> 00:05:59.899
Somebody save me

00:05:59.899 --> 00:05:59.980
Somebody save me

00:05:59.980 --> 00:06:00.000
Somebody save me

00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:05.879
Let your warm hands break right through

00:06:05.879 --> 00:06:10.860
So let it save me

00:06:10.860 --> 00:06:16.459
Don't care how you do it

00:06:16.459 --> 00:06:20.720
Just stay, stay

00:06:20.720 --> 00:06:26.459
Come on, I've been waiting for you

00:06:26.459 --> 00:06:29.720
Just stay with me

00:06:30.000 --> 00:06:37.060
I've made this whole world shine for you

00:06:37.060 --> 00:06:40.519
Just stay, stay

00:06:40.519 --> 00:06:42.500
Come on

00:06:42.500 --> 00:06:52.399
The distributor gets 12.5

00:06:52.399 --> 00:06:54.759
Feet bill over six months at 5%

00:06:54.759 --> 00:06:57.040
Plus the mortgage at 8.2

00:06:57.040 --> 00:06:59.259
Plus the harvester repairs gives us

00:06:59.259 --> 00:06:59.759
$54,000

00:07:00.000 --> 00:07:01.839
$501.38

00:07:01.839 --> 00:07:05.139
Hey, uh, son

00:07:05.139 --> 00:07:06.360
Look, I'm sorry

00:07:06.360 --> 00:07:07.920
We didn't need you to hear all that

00:07:07.920 --> 00:07:09.139
You don't have to protect me

00:07:09.139 --> 00:07:09.899
Is it that bad?

00:07:10.180 --> 00:07:11.240
Yeah, it's pretty bad

00:07:11.240 --> 00:07:12.680
We might have to take out a bank loan

00:07:12.680 --> 00:07:13.360
Another one?

00:07:13.420 --> 00:07:14.839
The interest alone would put us up to

00:07:14.839 --> 00:07:15.899
Clark, don't

00:07:15.899 --> 00:07:18.199
Maybe I can help

00:07:18.199 --> 00:07:19.079
You already have

00:07:19.079 --> 00:07:21.139
Last season you saved us four part-time hands

00:07:21.139 --> 00:07:22.300
I'm thinking bigger picture

00:07:22.300 --> 00:07:24.379
You know, forget about this whole high school thing

00:07:24.379 --> 00:07:26.579
And try for a pro sports team

00:07:26.579 --> 00:07:28.160
I could make a ton of money in endorsements

00:07:30.000 --> 00:07:32.100
Just trying to lighten up the mood

00:07:32.100 --> 00:07:35.500
Much as we'd love to see your face on a cereal box

00:07:35.500 --> 00:07:37.779
We'd settle for you getting to school on time

00:07:37.779 --> 00:07:38.160
Right

00:07:38.160 --> 00:07:42.699
Forgot

00:07:42.699 --> 00:07:45.660
That's $65,200

00:07:45.660 --> 00:07:46.220
Go

00:07:46.220 --> 00:07:46.879
And one

00:07:46.879 --> 00:07:52.339
So did Sean call?

00:07:53.120 --> 00:07:53.480
Negative

00:07:53.480 --> 00:07:55.899
Not that I was waiting by the phone or anything

00:07:55.899 --> 00:07:57.500
Maybe he got caught up

00:07:57.500 --> 00:07:59.879
One time my sister didn't hear from a guy for a week

00:07:59.879 --> 00:08:01.399
Once she called to tell him off

00:08:01.399 --> 00:08:02.540
Turned out his grandmother died

00:08:02.540 --> 00:08:05.079
As much as I appreciate the spotlight here, I'm fine

00:08:05.079 --> 00:08:06.620
You're probably better off

00:08:06.620 --> 00:08:08.180
Sean's a total dog anyway

00:08:08.180 --> 00:08:09.439
He's not that bad, Clark

00:08:09.439 --> 00:08:11.240
He's always been cool to me

00:08:11.240 --> 00:08:13.560
Just because you can't get past your Lana crush

00:08:13.560 --> 00:08:15.519
Don't knock the rest of us for trying to make a love connection

00:08:15.519 --> 00:08:17.019
I thought we were focusing on me here

00:08:17.019 --> 00:08:18.100
I don't have a crush on Lana

00:08:18.100 --> 00:08:19.399
Then why don't you ask some other girl out?

00:08:19.459 --> 00:08:19.920
Like who?

00:08:20.060 --> 00:08:20.480
Like Chloe

00:08:20.480 --> 00:08:21.180
Okay, wait

00:08:21.180 --> 00:08:24.759
I'm not some crash test dummy you guys can use to try out your dating skills

00:08:24.759 --> 00:08:25.259
You

00:08:25.259 --> 00:08:27.000
If you like Lana so much

00:08:27.000 --> 00:08:28.980
Why don't you just ask her out and get it over with?

00:08:29.040 --> 00:08:29.399
And you

00:08:29.399 --> 00:08:32.179
Stop acting like a Vegas bookie picks your dates

00:08:32.179 --> 00:08:33.179
And both of you

00:08:33.179 --> 00:08:34.259
Treat me better

00:08:49.579 --> 00:08:51.360
This is the flu season, young man

00:08:51.360 --> 00:08:52.980
I don't even know why you came in today

00:08:52.980 --> 00:08:55.159
I felt fine this morning

00:08:55.159 --> 00:08:57.639
Now I can't get warm

00:08:57.639 --> 00:08:58.600
Let's see

00:08:58.600 --> 00:08:59.100
Okay

00:08:59.399 --> 00:09:04.259
This can't be right

00:09:04.259 --> 00:09:05.480
You're not a popsicle

00:09:05.480 --> 00:09:07.139
Let's try again

00:09:07.139 --> 00:09:09.779
Here we go

00:09:17.639 --> 00:09:19.059
You're giving me the chills

00:09:19.059 --> 00:09:20.279
I'm sending you home

00:09:20.279 --> 00:09:26.279
I'm actually feeling a little better now

00:09:26.279 --> 00:09:28.039
Thanks

00:09:29.399 --> 00:09:35.179
Jacob get out of here

00:09:35.860 --> 00:09:38.279
Alliance

00:09:39.360 --> 00:09:40.240
overlay

00:09:40.240 --> 00:09:42.199
Whoa

00:09:42.199 --> 00:09:42.799
I come in peace

00:09:42.799 --> 00:09:46.819
I'm so sorry

00:09:46.819 --> 00:09:47.559
I didn't hear you

00:09:47.559 --> 00:09:48.819
I'm just glad you weren't welding

00:09:48.819 --> 00:09:51.419
What brings you out here in the middle of the day?

00:09:51.879 --> 00:09:53.059
Those artichokes are yours

00:09:53.059 --> 00:09:54.819
I need about 30 of them if you got them

00:09:54.819 --> 00:09:55.279
30?

00:09:55.419 --> 00:09:56.519
That's a lot of artichokes

00:09:56.519 --> 00:09:57.699
I'm hosting a dinner tomorrow night

00:09:57.699 --> 00:09:58.899
for the local farming community

00:09:58.899 --> 00:09:59.220
I'm not going to be there tomorrow night

00:09:59.220 --> 00:10:01.360
Just to inform, we'll talk about some financial options.

00:10:01.860 --> 00:10:03.460
A lot of farms in town are having money trouble.

00:10:03.800 --> 00:10:05.700
Most people aren't looking for more loans.

00:10:06.220 --> 00:10:07.720
I'm offering my role as an investor.

00:10:09.639 --> 00:10:11.779
Help people modernize and expand.

00:10:12.860 --> 00:10:15.540
This town once grew 20% of the corn in the state.

00:10:16.139 --> 00:10:17.120
Smallville was a heavy hitter.

00:10:17.220 --> 00:10:19.460
It just lost the drive to stay competitive.

00:10:20.060 --> 00:10:20.960
Or its connections.

00:10:21.580 --> 00:10:23.320
If this town ever had connections,

00:10:23.399 --> 00:10:24.560
they wouldn't have named it Smallville.

00:10:29.220 --> 00:10:32.080
Your husband hasn't exactly kept his feelings about me a secret.

00:10:32.580 --> 00:10:34.300
But I'd appreciate hearing your thoughts on my proposal,

00:10:34.399 --> 00:10:35.399
even if you're not interested.

00:10:36.120 --> 00:10:37.440
Jonathan doesn't hate you.

00:10:37.840 --> 00:10:41.800
It's just your family's track record hasn't been the best in this town.

00:10:42.000 --> 00:10:43.320
Tell him I intend to change that.

00:10:57.879 --> 00:10:58.279
Yeah.

00:10:59.220 --> 00:11:01.540
That's a great exhibit.

00:11:02.000 --> 00:11:02.980
Caught it in St. Petersburg.

00:11:03.720 --> 00:11:05.279
Whitney and I are going to Metropolis tomorrow.

00:11:05.379 --> 00:11:06.200
I thought we'd check it out.

00:11:06.600 --> 00:11:08.560
Ah, trying to give the quarterback some culture?

00:11:09.180 --> 00:11:10.120
That was his idea.

00:11:10.779 --> 00:11:12.279
He figures one afternoon at the museum,

00:11:12.379 --> 00:11:13.500
he's off the hook for six months.

00:11:14.259 --> 00:11:16.480
For someone who wants people to keep an open mind,

00:11:16.580 --> 00:11:17.779
you're pretty quick to judge.

00:11:19.540 --> 00:11:20.379
What can I say?

00:11:20.420 --> 00:11:21.680
I just think you're with the wrong guy.

00:11:26.620 --> 00:11:27.019
Hey.

00:11:29.220 --> 00:11:29.720
Hey.

00:11:30.100 --> 00:11:30.820
Everything okay?

00:11:31.460 --> 00:11:33.860
Yeah, I was just checking out some stuff for us to do tomorrow.

00:11:36.500 --> 00:11:37.980
Metropolis, remember?

00:11:42.680 --> 00:11:44.620
Actually, some of the guys are pulling together

00:11:44.720 --> 00:11:46.120
and getting the fight on pay-per-view.

00:11:47.540 --> 00:11:48.320
It's tomorrow.

00:11:49.899 --> 00:11:51.500
And you gave them your money already.

00:11:53.899 --> 00:11:54.399
Yeah.

00:11:56.700 --> 00:11:58.399
Hey, we'll go next weekend, okay?

00:11:58.460 --> 00:11:59.040
I promise.

00:11:59.220 --> 00:11:59.460
Okay.

00:12:01.460 --> 00:12:02.720
I'm really sorry, Lana.

00:12:03.500 --> 00:12:04.580
Culture can wait.

00:12:05.800 --> 00:12:06.740
Make it up to you.

00:12:08.519 --> 00:12:09.120
Let's go.

00:12:24.920 --> 00:12:26.700
You know, she's free tomorrow night.

00:12:27.700 --> 00:12:28.379
Hey, Clark.

00:12:29.220 --> 00:12:29.720
Yeah.

00:12:29.800 --> 00:12:31.740
This is the perfect time for you to ask her out.

00:12:31.820 --> 00:12:33.639
She's got a boyfriend, Lex.

00:12:34.600 --> 00:12:36.180
A high school boyfriend isn't a husband.

00:12:36.259 --> 00:12:37.220
He's an obstacle.

00:12:38.220 --> 00:12:39.899
Now, I bet if you ask Lana to go with you

00:12:39.980 --> 00:12:41.600
to the Radiohead concert in Metropolis tomorrow,

00:12:41.700 --> 00:12:42.560
she'll say yes.

00:12:44.100 --> 00:12:46.940
If she says yes, I'll give you the tickets.

00:12:50.320 --> 00:12:51.139
Why are you doing this?

00:12:52.420 --> 00:12:54.019
You're like the younger brother I never had.

00:12:54.639 --> 00:12:56.600
I figure someone should benefit from my experience.

00:12:57.060 --> 00:12:58.000
You can't just ask her out.

00:12:58.100 --> 00:12:59.200
The hardest thing in the world is to ask her out.

00:12:59.460 --> 00:13:00.940
You gotta ask her out.

00:13:01.040 --> 00:13:02.580
It's the first thing we do as a couple.

00:13:02.680 --> 00:13:03.639
I wanna think about how the ekler team

00:13:03.720 --> 00:13:04.660
must work together.

00:13:06.960 --> 00:13:08.860
There's no point in telling me

00:13:08.920 --> 00:13:10.320
that this good country girl from your world

00:13:10.399 --> 00:13:12.560
is telling the girl you love that you like her.

00:13:13.120 --> 00:13:15.100
Speaker 6.

00:13:15.180 --> 00:13:16.899
I'm Vit.

00:13:16.960 --> 00:13:18.720
You ask her in the next 60 seconds,

00:13:18.800 --> 00:13:19.580
you get the tickets,

00:13:19.660 --> 00:13:20.580
and I'll throwin' a round-trip limo ride.

00:13:20.639 --> 00:13:21.220
Starting.

00:13:22.680 --> 00:13:23.840
now?

00:13:23.920 --> 00:13:24.259
© Transcription Found by radiation-insight,

00:13:24.259 --> 00:13:25.540
USA

00:13:26.399 --> 00:13:27.500
Hilary, you busy?

00:13:27.580 --> 00:13:28.340
Completely swamped.

00:13:28.420 --> 00:13:28.940
Block imaginable.

00:13:28.940 --> 00:13:30.640
to wade through a Russian classic.

00:13:32.940 --> 00:13:34.280
That was a joke, Clark.

00:13:36.560 --> 00:13:37.700
Uh, good.

00:13:38.620 --> 00:13:40.660
Cause there's this thing tomorrow night.

00:13:40.660 --> 00:13:41.820
Defined thing?

00:13:42.800 --> 00:13:43.720
It's a concert.

00:13:43.720 --> 00:13:46.860
Radio had to be exact and I get a couple tickets.

00:13:46.860 --> 00:13:48.960
Wow, where'd you get these?

00:13:50.520 --> 00:13:52.180
A friend, something came up at the last minute

00:13:52.180 --> 00:13:55.180
and I was wondering if you'd like to go, you know, with me.

00:13:57.220 --> 00:13:58.420
I'd...

00:13:58.419 --> 00:13:59.419
be just as friends.

00:14:02.799 --> 00:14:04.799
Definitely. I'd love to.

00:14:09.219 --> 00:14:11.019
Okay, let me get this straight.

00:14:11.019 --> 00:14:12.639
You walked in to get a cappuccino

00:14:12.639 --> 00:14:14.899
and walked out with a date with Lana Lang.

00:14:14.899 --> 00:14:16.439
Well, it's not actually a date.

00:14:16.439 --> 00:14:19.059
Even with a just as friends rider, I'm impressed.

00:14:19.059 --> 00:14:20.360
How did you score the tickets?

00:14:20.360 --> 00:14:21.500
I'm guessing a certain

00:14:21.500 --> 00:14:24.099
follicly challenged individual was behind it.

00:14:24.099 --> 00:14:25.259
Lex hooked me up.

00:14:25.259 --> 00:14:26.899
Actually, Chloe, I have you to thank.

00:14:26.899 --> 00:14:27.740
What did I do?

00:14:27.740 --> 00:14:28.360
Well, you were right.

00:14:28.360 --> 00:14:30.259
I just had to get it out there.

00:14:30.259 --> 00:14:31.100
Well, good.

00:14:31.100 --> 00:14:31.899
I'm glad.

00:14:36.740 --> 00:14:38.139
Maybe this is your chance.

00:14:41.039 --> 00:14:44.600
Chloe, don't I owe you a phone call?

00:14:44.600 --> 00:14:45.680
I guess so.

00:14:45.680 --> 00:14:47.539
Well, what are you doing right now?

00:14:47.539 --> 00:14:49.580
Well, I've got to put the paper to bed.

00:14:49.580 --> 00:14:51.980
Maybe afterwards we can, you know, do something.

00:14:54.899 --> 00:14:56.680
Jenna, Jenna, wait up.

00:14:58.360 --> 00:15:02.259
Jenna,

00:15:02.259 --> 00:15:03.200
What's going on?

00:15:03.200 --> 00:15:05.800
Ok, I was playing barely hard to get.

00:15:05.800 --> 00:15:07.460
What's the problem?

00:15:09.539 --> 00:15:11.120
Clark Kent gets a date with Lana Lang

00:15:11.120 --> 00:15:14.600
and suddenly there is no luck left for the rest of us.

00:15:14.620 --> 00:15:16.620
Oh, look who we have here.

00:15:21.240 --> 00:15:24.279
See, doesn't she look like a cheeky wealthy young lady?

00:15:24.279 --> 00:15:25.120
Check this out.

00:15:25.120 --> 00:15:25.899
This is...

00:15:25.899 --> 00:15:26.659
What?

00:15:26.659 --> 00:15:27.820
What?

